#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/smoothing.rst:24
msgid ""
"As seen in the previous sections, polygons are central to Blender. Most "
"objects are represented by polygons and truly curved objects are often "
"approximated by polygon meshes. When rendering images, you may notice that "
"these polygons appear as a series of small, flat faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/smoothing.rst:29
msgid ""
"Sometimes this is a desirable effect, but usually we want our objects to "
"look nice and smooth. This section shows you how to visually smooth an "
"object, and how to apply the *Auto Smooth* filter to quickly and easily "
"combine smooth and faceted polygons in the same object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/smoothing.rst:33
msgid ""
"The last section on this page shows possibilities for smoothing a mesh's "
"geometry, not only its appearance."
msgstr ""

